<h3>Referral Data Preservation</h3>
<p>When a user clicks from an HTTPS site to an HTTP site, the referral data is stripped. Your analytics show the visit as "direct" traffic instead of identifying the referring source. This means you lose visibility into where your traffic actually comes from.</p>
<p>HTTPS to HTTPS referrals preserve the full referral chain. Accurate attribution data leads to better marketing decisions.</p>
<h3>HTTP/2 and HTTP/3 Performance</h3>
<p>Modern web protocols like HTTP/2 and HTTP/3 require HTTPS. These protocols deliver faster page loads through multiplexing, header compression, and connection reuse. Sites on HTTP are stuck on HTTP/1.1, which loads resources sequentially and runs slower.</p>
<p>Faster page speed is a confirmed ranking factor. HTTPS enables the protocols that make your site faster.</p>
