<h3>What to Monitor</h3>
<p>Check Google Search Console daily during the first 2 weeks after migration:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Coverage report:</strong> Look for indexing errors, excluded pages, or crawl anomalies</li>
<li><strong>Performance report:</strong> Compare impressions and clicks to pre-migration baseline</li>
<li><strong>URL Inspection tool:</strong> Test individual pages to verify Google sees the HTTPS version</li>
</ul>
<p>Check for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Pages returning 404 (broken redirects)</li>
<li>Redirect chains (HTTP → HTTPS → another HTTPS URL)</li>
<li>Redirect loops (page A redirects to page B which redirects back to page A)</li>
<li>Pages still indexed as HTTP (submit them for reindexing)</li>
</ul>
<h3>If Rankings Do Not Recover</h3>
<p>If traffic has not returned after 6 weeks, check these common causes:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Missing 301 redirects.</strong> Run a crawl and compare HTTP URLs to their HTTPS counterparts.</li>
<li><strong>Canonical tags still pointing to HTTP.</strong> Every canonical must reference the HTTPS URL.</li>
<li><strong>Sitemap still listing HTTP URLs.</strong> Resubmit the HTTPS sitemap.</li>
<li><strong>Mixed content blocking full HTTPS evaluation.</strong> Fix all HTTP resources.</li>
<li><strong>Certificate expiry.</strong> An expired certificate triggers browser warnings and ranking drops.</li>
</ol>
